ciscoSwitchRateLimiterMIB.name: ciscoSwitchRateLimiterMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoSwitchRateLimiterMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-lan-switch-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoSwitchRateLimiterMIB.description: This MIB module defines management objects for the Switch Rate Limiter features on Cisco Layer 2 and Layer 3 devices. Rate limits prevents redirected control packets for egress exceptions from overwhelming the supervisor module on a device.

csrlRateLimiterClassTable.name: csrlRateLimiterClassTable
csrlRateLimiterClassTable.description: A table containing descriptions of the rate limiter classes supported by the device.

csrlRateLimiterClassEntry.name: csrlRateLimiterClassEntry
csrlRateLimiterClassEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the description of a particular rate limiter class.

csrlRateLimiterClassId.name: csrlRateLimiterClassId
csrlRateLimiterClassId.description: An arbitrary positive integer value that uniquely identifies a rate limiter class.

csrlRateLimiterClassDescr.name: csrlRateLimiterClassDescr
csrlRateLimiterClassDescr.description: This object indicates the description of the rate limiter class.

csrlGlobalRateLimiterTable.name: csrlGlobalRateLimiterTable
csrlGlobalRateLimiterTable.description: A table containing global configuration and statistics of rate limiter classes.

csrlGlobalRateLimiterEntry.name: csrlGlobalRateLimiterEntry
csrlGlobalRateLimiterEntry.description: A conceptual row containing global management information of a particular rate limiter class.

csrlGlobalRateLimiterConfigured.name: csrlGlobalRateLimiterConfigured
csrlGlobalRateLimiterConfigured.description: This object specifies the global rate limit configured for this rate limiter class. The global rate limit for this class is applied to every entity which does not have its local rate limit of same class configured, the value of the corresponding csrlLocalRateLimiterConfigured is -2. A value of -1 indicates that the global rate limit for this rate limiter class is disabled. A value of 0 indicates that the system does not allow any packets for this rate limiter class to go through the supervisor.

csrlGlobalRateLimiterAllowed.name: csrlGlobalRateLimiterAllowed
csrlGlobalRateLimiterAllowed.description: This object indicates the number of packets allowed globally for this rate limiter class. When the value of csrlGlobalRateLimiterConfigured is -1, the value of this object is always 0.

csrlGlobalRateLimiterDropped.name: csrlGlobalRateLimiterDropped
csrlGlobalRateLimiterDropped.description: This object indicates the number of packets which have been dropped globally for this rate limiter class. When the value of csrlGlobalRateLimiterConfigured is -1, the value of this object is always 0.

csrlGlobalRateLimiterTotal.name: csrlGlobalRateLimiterTotal
csrlGlobalRateLimiterTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of packets have been processed globally for this rate limiter class. When the value of csrlGlobalRateLimiterConfigured is -1, the value of this object is always 0.

csrlLocalRateLimiterTable.name: csrlLocalRateLimiterTable
csrlLocalRateLimiterTable.description: A table containing local rate limiter configuration and statistics for a specific entity. For Example: A module on the device. A set of rate limiter class entries are added to this table when a rate limiter capable entity comes online. The same set of entries are deleted from this table when the entity goes offline.

csrlLocalRateLimiterEntry.name: csrlLocalRateLimiterEntry
csrlLocalRateLimiterEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the local rate limiter management information for a particular rate limiter capable entity.

csrlLocalRateLimiterConfigured.name: csrlLocalRateLimiterConfigured
csrlLocalRateLimiterConfigured.description: This object specifies the local rate limit configured for this rate limiter class on this entity. A value of -2 indicates that the entity does not have local rate limiter configured, and will pick up the configuration from csrlGlobalRateLimiterConfigured. A value of -1 indicates that this rate limiter class is disabled locally for this entity. A value of 0 indicates that the rate limiter does not allow any packets from this entity for this rate limiter class to go through the supervisor.

csrlLocalRateLimiterAllowed.name: csrlLocalRateLimiterAllowed
csrlLocalRateLimiterAllowed.description: This object indicates the number of packets allowed on this entity for this rate limiter class. When the value of csrlLocalRateLimiterConfigured is -1, the value of this object is always 0.

csrlLocalRateLimiterDropped.name: csrlLocalRateLimiterDropped
csrlLocalRateLimiterDropped.description: This object indicates the number of packets dropped on this entity for this rate limiter class. When the value of csrlLocalRateLimiterConfigured is -1, the value of this object is always 0.

csrlLocalRateLimiterTotal.name: csrlLocalRateLimiterTotal
csrlLocalRateLimiterTotal.description: This object indicates the number of packets processed on this entity for this rate limiter class. When the value of csrlLocalRateLimiterConfigured is -1, the value of this object is always 0.

csrlRateLimiterClassGroup.name: csrlRateLimiterClassGroup
csrlRateLimiterClassGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Rate Limiter Class information.

csrlGlobalRateLimiterGroup.name: csrlGlobalRateLimiterGroup
csrlGlobalRateLimiterGroup.description: A collection of objects providing global rate limiter information.

csrlLocalRateLimiterGroup.name: csrlLocalRateLimiterGroup
csrlLocalRateLimiterGroup.description: A collection of objects providing local rate limiter information.
